// =============================================================================
// FileSync — Distributed File-Sharing & Replicated Storage System
// =============================================================================
//
// Protocol Buffers v3 service definition for the FileSync distributed system.
//
// This proto file defines ALL gRPC services and messages required for:
//   1. File Operations      — Upload, Download, Delete, ListFiles
//   2. Snapshot Management   — CreateSnapshot, ListSnapshots, ReadSnapshot
//   3. Leader Election       — Heartbeat, Election, ElectionVictory (Bully Algorithm)
//   4. Mutual Exclusion      — ForwardWrite (Centralized Server approach)
//   5. Replication           — ReplicateFile (async master → follower replication)
//   6. Checkpointing         — CheckpointRequest (Koo-Toueg inspired coordination)
//
// Physical Architecture:
//   - 4 independent nodes on a LAN (~10ms RTT)
//   - Tolerates 1 node failure
//   - Master elected via Bully Algorithm (300ms heartbeat timeout, 85ms convergence)
//
// Author: FileSync Team
// =============================================================================

